$ Microsoft Outlook
@ Outlook

{ Changing some annoying predefined settings

  { Don't automatically mark as unread
  
    → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Mail/Outlook-panes[File -> Options -> Mail -> Outlook-panes], button *Reading Pane* -> Uncheck *Mark item as read when selection changes*.
  
  }
  { Don't show a notification when a message arrives

    Disable *Play a sound* and *Display a Desktop Alert* under → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Mail/Message-arrival[File -> Options Mail -> Message arrival]

  }
  { Put email content below inbox
  
    Go to ~Mail~ (not *Calendar*, *Contacts* or *Tasks*) -> View (the ribbon tab) -> Reading Pane -> Bottom
  
  }
  { Show one line only per message in the inbox

    View -> Message Preview -> Off

  }
  { Add signature


    In → https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/create-and-add-an-email-signature-in-outlook-8ee5d4f4-68fd-464a-a1c1-0e1c80bb27f2#PickTab=Classic_Outlook[classic outlook]:
      • → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Home[Home] -> New -> New Mail, then in the message

  }

}
{ Switch between working offline and working online

  Menu *Send/Receive* -> group *Preferences* -> toggle *Work Offline*.

}
{ Pasting content

  Ribbon tab *Message*, then → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Message/Clipboard/Paste[Clipboard -> Paste].

}
{ OST and PST files #outlook-ost-pst-files

  PST stands for *Personal Store*.
  -
  These files store the data of the personal folders, such as (?) emails, contacts, tasks and calendar.

  OST stands for *Offline Store*.
  -
  These files store the data that was (previously) downloaded from an → Microsoft/products/Exchange[Exchange Server].

? The (a?) PST file is stored under → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Local/Microsoft/Outlook/username-at-domain_ost[`%LOCALAPPDATA%\Microsoft\Outlook\username@domain.ost`]

  See also
    • the → Windows/registry[registry] key → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Outlook/PST[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\X.Y\Outlook\PST`]
    • The `filePath` property of the → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/Object-Model/Store[`store` object]
    • → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/SCANPST_EXE[`SCANPST.EXE`], the Outlook Inbox Repair Tool

}
{ Exchange ActiveSync

 *Exchange ActiveSync* is the synchronization protocol for Microsoft Exchange.

}

sa:

  The → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/Outlook[PowerShell module `Outlook`] allows to send mails from the command line.

  → Microsoft/products/Exchange#determine-exchange-version[Determine the Exchange version] that Outlook is connected to.

  → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/Object-Model

  → Microsoft/Office

  → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Local/Microsoft/Outlook
